nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If they have no singleton or void they bid game (4@S here) showing a minimum opener with no slam interest.|
PG| ***** 50 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Or 3NT showing a medium opener (15-17 or so) with no singleton.|
PG| ***** 51 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Or 3@S showing a strong opener (18+) and intends to bid slam if they have controls in all of the suits.|
PG| ***** 52 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There is one other response that occurs very infrequently that many don't even know about that happens to apply here. That is a jump to 4 of a suit showing a 5-card side suit with 2 of the top 3 honors which can be a powerful source of tricks and will sometimes allow you to bid a grand slam.|
